  <intervention>
    <intervention_type>Other</intervention_type>
    <intervention_name>Motor exercises for swallowing, breathing and phonation</intervention_name>
    <description>This exercises aimed to increase strength and range of motion of mouth, larynx and pharynx structures. All patients made sustained vowel phonation of /a/, pushing plosive phonemes /pa/, /ta/, /ka/ in a forceful manner, suction of wet gauze, swallowing with tongue hold and modified supraglottic maneuver, in ten repetitions, ascending and descending gliding phonation of vowel /a/ and /u/, five repetitions of each vowel, and tongue rotation in oral vestibule, 3 series of 5 repetitions to each side. Patients underwent oral motor exercises twice a day, five days a week, for five weeks.</description>
    <arm_group_label>Swallowing exercises</arm_group_label>
  </intervention>
